are_the_advantages_of_PPF_coating\" title=\"What are the advantages of PPF coating?&#xA0;\">What are the advantages of PPF coating?&#xA0;<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-12\" href=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/ppf-coating\/#What_are_the_disadvantages_of_PPF_coating\" title=\"What are the disadvantages of PPF coating?&#xA0;\">What are the disadvantages of PPF coating?&#xA0;<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-13\" href=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/ppf-coating\/#Will_bubbles_in_PPF_go_away\" title=\"Will bubbles in PPF go away?&#xA0;\">Will bubbles in PPF go away?&#xA0;<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-14\" href=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/ppf-coating\/#How_strong_is_PPF_film\" title=\"How strong is PPF film?&#xA0;\">How strong is PPF film?&#xA0;<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-15\" href=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/ppf-coating\/#Can_you_remove_PPF\" title=\"Can you remove PPF?&#xA0;\">Can you remove PPF?&#xA0;<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-16\" href=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/ppf-coating\/#Does_PPF_increase_resale_value\" title=\"Does PPF increase resale value?&#xA0;\">Does PPF increase resale value?&#xA0;<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-17\" href=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/ppf-coating\/#Conclusion\" title=\"Conclusion\">Conclusion<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/nav><\/div>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"What_is_Paint_Protection_Film\"><\/span><b>What is Paint Protection Film?<\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The paints protection film is a car paint protection film which helps in defending your vehicle&#8217;s paint finish against scratches and blemishes. These films are installed after a car wash and help in protecting your vehicle from dirt and contaminants. It also helps in reducing glare on windows and windscreens of vehicles. These films are durable, and resistant to water damage, UV damage, and scratching. Paints protection film reduces the maintenance cost of vehicles because it can last up to 7 years or more as compared to traditional car paints which need constant polishing and washing. Some PPF Films come with additional benefits such as heat reduction capacity of around 5%, reduces reflection in front window glass by 85% &amp; adds an extra layer of privacy for cars with black tinted windows.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"The_Effectiveness_of_Paint_Protection_Film\"><\/span><b>The Effectiveness of Paint Protection Film<\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The paint protection film is becoming a more and more popular option for both new cars and as an aftermarket upgrade. This is because there are many benefits that paint protection film has to offer. Not only does it make your car look great, but it can also help protect your car from scratches and scuffs. Some people even prefer paint protection film over regular clear coats. Here we&#x2019;ll take a closer look at how effective paint protection film actually is and if it&#x2019;s worth investing in for your vehicle.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Is_Paint_Protection_Film_Safe\"><\/span><b>Is Paint Protection Film Safe?<\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">When purchasing a car it&#x2019;s easy to get caught up in its appearance. After all, you want a car that looks good and will stand out amongst other vehicles on your street. While it&#x2019;s fun to customize your vehicle with new rims and wheels or maybe even a nice new paint job when you do add anything new it can damage your paint causing it to crack or flake off. The paint protection film is applied before any damage is done and provides extra durability against scratches and rock chips.&#xA0;<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Which_Type_of_PPF_Coatings_Are_Most_Popular\"><\/span><b>Which Type of PPF Coatings Are Most Popular?<\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The most popular PPF coating available on today&#x2019;s market is called ceramic. It offers incredible paint protection and will come in at a mid-range price point. The next popular choice is polyurethane&#x2014;this option doesn&#x2019;t last as long as ceramic but still offers great protection at a fraction of ceramic&#x2019;s cost. UltraViolet absorbers are also available but require more maintenance.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"How_Much_Does_it_Cost\"><\/span><b>How Much Does it Cost?<\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Depending on the car&#8217;s size and model, It starts from 14999 at VehicleCare.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"PPF_coating_products\"><\/span><b>PPF coating products<\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">For those who don&#x2019;t know, PPF is a clear-coat product made of polyurethane. It forms a chemical bond with your vehicle&#x2019;s paintwork and protects it from sun damage that can otherwise make your vehicle look dull. If you want to keep your car shiny and rust-free for as long as possible, the coating is one of the best things you can do. Here are some tips on what it is, why you need it, and how much it costs for each application.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"PPF_coating_process\"><\/span><b>PPF coating process<\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The first thing you&#8217;ll want to do is decide what kind of pf coating process you&#8217;d like. PPF coating process comes in two forms: a 2-part system and a 3-part system. The 2-part involves applying a primer directly onto your car&#8217;s paint and then layering on top of that with a second coat for optimal coverage. With a 3-part system, you start off by layering your car with filler and then spraying down another layer over top of that. When it&#8217;s dry, spray down one last layer before wet sanding with medium-grit sandpaper; follow up by buffing out any high spots with low grit sandpaper.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"PPF_coating_vs_ceramic_coating\"><\/span><b>PPF coating vs ceramic coating<\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This distinction is important because even though both are strong and durable, they have some distinct advantages over one another. Generally speaking, the ceramic coating offers a much smoother finish than PPF coating. PPF coating has a gritty texture that many people find ugly. In addition to aesthetics, there are also some functional advantages of ceramic coating over PPF. The harder surface of ceramic coatings makes them less susceptible to stone chips than their softer counterparts&#8230; more<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"PPF_coating_for_bikes\"><\/span><b>PPF coating for bikes<\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Knowing what you&#8217;re buying is just as important for your car or bike. This PPF coating for bikes review will tell you all about price, application, installation, and whether it&#8217;s worth using. It seems that more and more people are considering getting their bikes coated in paint protection film of some kind. But why? There is a huge range of different types of film available on a number of websites like Amazon with very different prices so which one should you choose? And what are you actually buying? Today we&#8217;ll be taking a look at PPF coating for bikes from the company VehicleCare to give an overview of what exactly it does and if it&#8217;s worth spending money on before you spend any cash! Let&#8217;s get started&#8230;<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"How_Long_Does_it_Take_to_Install_the_PPF_on_My_Car\"><\/span><b>How Long Does it Take to Install the PPF on My Car?<\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The prep time required before coating installation depends on a few factors. If it&#x2019;s new and clean, then you&#x2019;ll need less time than someone who has an older car that hasn&#x2019;t been detailed in years. Another factor affecting how long PPF takes to install is how many cars are being coated on a single day. Larger body shops have more customers and will naturally take longer than smaller companies or single-car operations.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"What_are_the_advantages_of_PPF_coating\"><\/span><b>What are the advantages of PPF coating?&#xA0;<\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The main advantage of a PPF coating is its protection. With one application, you are able to protect your vehicle for many years. No matter how often you wash it or drive through a car wash, your vehicle will always look as good as new. Moreover, PPF coatings are very effective in protecting your vehicle against discoloration and fading. They can also block out any other damage that can occur from chemicals and industrial fallout. If you&#x2019;re living in an area where it&#x2019;s common for roads to be covered with chemicals from factories and other businesses, having a coating on your car will help keep it looking great year after year.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"What_are_the_disadvantages_of_PPF_coating\"><\/span><b>What are the disadvantages of PPF coating?&#xA0;<\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">With car care products, everything comes with its pros and cons. There&#x2019;s nothing that&#x2019;s perfect in our world. Since we are talking about PPF coating, let&#x2019;s have a look at some of its cons. First of all, PPF is not only expensive but also time-consuming. It will take a good deal of your time for applying it to your vehicle in different phases. Because it has to be done carefully one part at a time and then left for drying before you can go onto another phase of it, you will end up spending a long amount of time doing your car care job each day you want to do so.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Will_bubbles_in_PPF_go_away\"><\/span><b>Will bubbles in PPF go away?&#xA0;<\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">There is no denying that most car enthusiasts like a nice shiny finish. But in order to maintain such a shiny finish, you will have to ensure that your paint protection film does not bubble. It may be an obvious statement but it is well worth mentioning. So if you plan on using PPF coating make sure that your paint protection film does not bubble. Thankfully there are options available which we will look at below. However, before moving on let us first discuss what causes PPFs bubbling and how it can be avoided? If a paint protection film was scratched or damaged it would allow air and moisture into the micro-pores of your car&#x2019;s paintwork where both cause damage and eventually lead to bubbles forming on top of your PPF film.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"How_strong_is_PPF_film\"><\/span><b>How strong is PPF film?&#xA0;<\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It&#x2019;s quite possible that you have heard of polymer film when it comes to having protection for vehicles. In reality, however, a variety of different materials are used in order to provide extra security. Polymer paint protection is a popular material used on all types of cars and trucks. While many people do not know what exactly they are buying when they opt for PPF or paint protection film at vehicle dealerships or shops throughout their areas, it is important that they know everything about it before making any final decisions. This way, people can determine whether or not it will be right for them and if so how long they should keep using it.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Can_you_remove_PPF\"><\/span><b>Can you remove PPF?&#xA0;<\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">PPF is commonly used as a protective coating for cars. It&#x2019;s durable and hard-wearing, but there are some situations where you might need to remove it. An application error or failure may have left your vehicle looking dull and unsightly. Alternatively, you may want to upgrade your car&#x2019;s look with something more stylish. No matter what kind of PPF installation you have on your car &#x2013; wet or dry &#x2013; we can help you remove it safely. Our state-of-the-art equipment includes sanders, abrasive blasting machines, and high-pressure washers that allow us to get rid of any old coatings while retaining all of your original paintworks underneath.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Does_PPF_increase_resale_value\"><\/span><b>Does PPF increase resale value?&#xA0;<\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">PPF stands for Paint Protection Film. This durable film is installed by professionals, typically on new vehicles. It&#8217;s made of polyurethane or polyester that&#8217;s UV-rated and resistant to minor scratches and scuffs. Most often, PPF is applied in a solid color; but for those who want more visual customization options, there are many paint protection film kits that include metallic colors and patterns. After installation by a professional who will align and cut out all necessary shapes (door handles, lights), a new layer of PPF can be up to 99 percent clear.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Conclusion\"><\/span><b>Conclusion<\/b><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Vehicle care is more than just washing your car with water and soap. Properly caring for your vehicle can make all of the difference between its lasting you a decade or being damaged beyond repair after a few years. Thankfully, with proper attention and maintenance, there&#8217;s no reason why your vehicle can&#8217;t last you much longer than it otherwise would. And we hope that by using our services, you&#8217;ll be able to get that much more out of it! In summary: what is PPF? It&#8217;s a protective film coating designed to protect your vehicle from chips and scratches as well as dirt build-up over time. Whether you live in a city or near construction sites or experience potholes on a regular basis&#8230;it&#8217;s worth it for any driver!<\/span><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>At first glance, you might think that a clear bra would be the best way to protect your car&#x2019;s finish from scratches and paint chips. But there&#x2019;s another solution available: Paint Protection Film (PPF).&#46;&#46;&#46;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":200029,"featured_media":2504,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[1],"tags":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pos